{
  slug === 'compress-to-exact-file-size' && <>
    <p>
      Need to squeeze an image under 100 KB for a form upload? Hit exactly 250 KB for a job application system? Or target 5 MB for an email attachment? Exact file size compression is one of the most requested features in any image tool — and most compressors force you to guess by adjusting a vague quality slider until you land in the right ballpark.
    </p>
    <p>
      ToolBox Image's target-size mode does this automatically. Tell it the maximum file size, and it finds the right quality level, format, and resolution to hit that target. Here is how to use it.
    </p>
    <h2>Why exact file size matters</h2>
    <p>
